id: pm-ch59
title: pm create/update mutation output always emits full changed_fields array (~50% of payload) with no way to suppress it
description: "Repro: PM_AUTHOR=x pm create issue 'probe' (default TOON). Observed: 21-line output where 11 lines are a 'changed_fields' array listing id,title,description,type,status,priority,tags,created_at,updated_at,author on EVERY create; update emits the same pattern. The item body directly above already shows the set values, so changed_fields is largely redundant for the create case. Expected: a way to trim mutation output for agent loops, e.g. accept --fields (already works on get, rejected on create with 'Unknown option --fields'), or a --quiet/--no-changed-fields, or drop the full changed_fields list on create (keep it on update where it signals the delta). Severity: low (token efficiency in high-volume agent create loops; ~50% of create payload is the redundant array). Note: prior verbosity item pm-3pbs was scoped to pm activity/history only, not mutations."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,dogfood,dx
created_at: "2026-05-25T18:30:34.477Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T20:25:05.565Z"
author: dogfood-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-25T18:30:41.628Z",dogfood-agent,"Dedup checks run against real tracker (no PM_PATH override) on 2026-05-25 before filing: (1) pm search 'create update changed_fields verbose suppress quiet flag' --limit 12 -> hits pm-rnpb(in_progress parent), pm-5k2w(init verbosity, closed), pm-swie/pm-ote/pm-j1v7/pm-phob/pm-kpz5/pm-wo8/pm-ysgr/pm-mfza/pm-06t (all unrelated create/update feature work, closed) -- none about output verbosity/changed_fields suppression. (2) pm search 'mutation output quiet compact' -> pm-3pbs (closed) reduces verbosity of pm ACTIVITY/HISTORY and adds compact mode to history, NOT create/update mutations -- scope differs. (3) pm list --status open --limit 30 -> pm-59gj,pm-gt82,pm-3cbk (none related). (4) pm list --status in-progress --limit 20 -> pm-rnpb,pm-7rlp,pm-cf1u (none related). Conclusion: no open or recently-closed item covers suppressing/trimming create/update mutation output. Filed as new under pm-rnpb."
  "2026-05-25T19:47:52.743Z",codex-full-audit,"Full audit confirmation: mutation JSON output remains a real token-efficiency issue and is not solved in this slice. Manual/sub-agent dogfood still shows bulky changed_fields/linked object payloads as a high-value optimization for agents. This pass focused on command recovery, package validation, SDK/package boundary, and vector cache correctness; leave pm-ch59 open for explicit compact mutation-output projection work."
  "2026-05-25T19:56:59.534Z",manual-dogfood-specialist,"Manual dogfood evidence 2026-05-25: create/update JSON outputs in the temp LaunchOps project still repeatedly emitted large changed_fields arrays. On first create, changed_fields listed id/title/description/type/status/priority/tags/created_at/updated_at/deadline/author/body; update with comment/note/learning emitted a full item plus changed_fields. This confirms the open token-cost concern remains relevant for agents; fields projections help reads but mutation outputs still need a compact/default projection or a way to suppress changed_fields without losing deterministic mutation evidence.\n"
  "2026-05-25T20:25:05.565Z",manual-dogfood-subagent,"Manual dogfood reconfirmed mutation output verbosity: create/update/claim/close/comment-style commands returned full item/comment payloads by default. In small temp project this was usable, but comments on pm-rnpb returned a massive historical comment array, reinforcing the need for compact mutation acknowledgements / suppressible changed_fields and append outputs for token efficiency."
body: ""
